ðŸ”¹ What is Autoboxing?
Autoboxing is the automatic conversion of a primitive type â†’ its corresponding wrapper class.
public class AutoBoxingExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a = 10;
        Integer b = a;  // autoboxing (int â†’ Integer)
        System.out.println(b); // Output: 10
    }
}
Here, Java automatically converts the primitive int into an Integer object.

ðŸ”¹ What is Unboxing?
The reverse process: Wrapper class â†’ primitive type.
Example-
public class UnboxingExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Integer a = 20;
        int b = a;  // unboxing (Integer â†’ int)
        System.out.println(b); // Output: 20
    }
}

âœ… In short:
Autoboxing = primitive â†’ wrapper.
Unboxing = wrapper â†’ primitive.



